2. THE EFFECTS OF SKIP CONNECTIONS
In this section, we analyze how skip connections inï¬‚uence backdoor attacks from both training and inference stages. We adopt ResNet-18 [16] on the CIFAR-10 dataset as an example for our discussions, as follows:
Training Stage. We introduce a decay factor Î³ âˆˆ [0, 1] to reduce gradients from the skip connections to suppress their effects. Our goal is to explore whether the suppression can alleviate the backdoor attack. The gradient suppression is conducted on all skip connections, as denoted in E.q.(1).

